important topics , no substance i approached this book with the utmost hopefulness since there has not been one to date on asian american youth . unfortunately , now that i am no longer in my teens i have a difficult time relating to their borderline cliche reflections . for sure the anthology could have done without the & quot ; now i 'm in this ivy league college & quot ; biographies and most of the poetry , about which i wonder if the authors wo n't be a bit embarrassed later on . this was a much-needed effort , but just because there is urgency does not warrant slack editing